    <title>Re: HTTP 400: "External account can't create application...</title>
    <updated>2024-11-25T20:35:11.140000+01:00</updated>
    <author>
      <name>gregorw</name>
      <uri>https://community.sap.com/t5/user/viewprofilepage/user-id/12545</uri>
    </author>
    <content>&lt;P&gt;Hello Luis,&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P&gt;seems to be the same problem that I just faced with the&amp;nbsp;&lt;A href="https://help.sap.com/docs/warehouse-operator?locale=en-US" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer"&gt;SAP Warehouse Operator&lt;/A&gt;&amp;nbsp;application. When the test environment was created in June it was possible to create the App ID with&amp;nbsp;&lt;SPAN&gt;com.sap.mobile.apps.warehouseoperator&lt;/SPAN&gt; following the documentation&amp;nbsp;&lt;A href="https://help.sap.com/docs/warehouse-operator/administration-guide/create-mobile-application?locale=en-US" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer"&gt;Create a Mobile Application&lt;/A&gt;. But when I tried now to create the App on a new instance of SAP Mobile Service for production I got the same error. I've filed a case via SAP support and contacted&amp;nbsp;&lt;a href="https://community.sap.com/t5/user/viewprofilepage/user-id/10613"&gt;@SamiLechner&lt;/a&gt;. Our Mobile Service instance was updated and allows now the creation of app IDs starting with com.sap. Now the onboarding of users to the Warehouse Operator App works as it seems that this SAP standard app checks the ID.&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P&gt;Best Regards&lt;BR /&gt;Gregor&lt;/P&gt;</content>
